{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0162GDMi7RSziWxN7Jazat7A","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Feature: Standard Preset Run Start Orchestration\n     2→  The `run start` command executes all stages of the standard flow preset\n     3→  end-to-end using the workflow engine, persisting validated payloads,\n     4→  rendered artifacts, journal events, and run snapshots at durable stage\n     5→  boundaries.\n     6→\n     7→  # SC-START-001\n     8→  Scenario: Happy path standard run completes all stages\n     9→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n    10→    And project \"alpha\" is selected as active\n    11→    And the run snapshot shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n    12→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    13→    Then the command exits successfully\n    14→    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n    15→    And the journal contains \"run_started\", \"stage_entered\", \"stage_completed\", and \"run_completed\" events\n    16→    And payload and artifact records exist for all 8 standard stages\n    17→\n    18→  # SC-START-002\n    19→  Scenario: Run start succeeds for quick_dev flow preset\n    20→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"beta\" using flow \"quick_dev\"\n    21→    And project \"beta\" is selected as active\n    22→    And the run snapshot shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n    23→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    24→    Then the command exits successfully\n    25→    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n    26→    And the journal records \"plan_and_implement\", \"review\", \"apply_fixes\", and \"final_review\" in sequence\n    27→    And payload and artifact records exist for all 4 quick_dev stages\n    28→\n    29→  # SC-START-003\n    30→  Scenario: Run start rejects already-running project\n    31→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"gamma\" using flow \"standard\"\n    32→    And project \"gamma\" is selected as active\n    33→    And the run snapshot shows status \"running\" with an active run\n    34→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    35→    Then the command fails with error containing \"not_started\"\n    36→    And the run snapshot is unchanged (still \"running\")\n    37→\n    38→  # SC-START-004\n    39→  Scenario: Run start rejects already-completed project\n    40→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"delta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    41→    And project \"delta\" is selected as active\n    42→    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n    43→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    44→    Then the command fails with error containing \"not_started\"\n    45→    And the run snapshot is unchanged (still \"completed\")\n    46→\n    47→  # SC-START-005\n    48→  Scenario: Run start validates workspace version before proceeding\n    49→    Given a workspace with unsupported version\n    50→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    51→    Then the command fails with error referencing workspace version\n    52→    And no run state is mutated\n    53→\n    54→  # SC-START-006\n    55→  Scenario: Run start requires an active project\n    56→    Given an initialized workspace with no active project\n    57→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    58→    Then the command fails with error referencing active project\n    59→    And no run state is mutated\n    60→\n    61→  # SC-START-007\n    62→  Scenario: Stage plan derives from flow definition with prompt_review enabled\n    63→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"echo\" using flow \"standard\"\n    64→    And prompt_review.enabled is true (default)\n    65→    When the stage plan is derived\n    66→    Then the plan includes all 8 standard stages in canonical order\n    67→    And the first stage is \"prompt_review\"\n    68→\n    69→  # SC-START-008\n    70→  Scenario: Stage plan skips prompt_review when disabled\n    71→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"foxtrot\" using flow \"standard\"\n    72→    And prompt_review.enabled is false\n    73→    When the stage plan is derived\n    74→    Then the plan includes 7 stages (all except prompt_review)\n    75→    And the first stage is \"planning\"\n    76→\n    77→  # SC-START-009\n    78→  Scenario: Preflight checks validate all stages before any mutation\n    79→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"golf\" using flow \"standard\"\n    80→    And the backend is unavailable\n    81→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    82→    Then the command fails with error containing \"preflight\"\n    83→    And the run snapshot is unchanged (still \"not_started\")\n    84→    And the journal has no new events beyond project_created\n    85→\n    86→  # SC-START-010\n    87→  Scenario: Stage-to-role mapping is deterministic\n    88→    Given the standard flow stage sequence\n    89→    Then each stage maps to exactly one backend role\n    90→    And the mapping is consistent across invocations\n    91→\n    92→  # SC-START-011\n    93→  Scenario: Atomic stage commit persists payload, artifact, journal event, and snapshot\n    94→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"hotel\" using flow \"standard\"\n    95→    And the run has started and is executing stages\n    96→    When a stage completes successfully\n    97→    Then a payload record is written to history/payloads\n    98→    And a matching artifact record is written to history/artifacts\n    99→    And a stage_completed event is appended to the journal\n   100→    And the run snapshot is updated with the next stage cursor"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Yb9w6C5ywNFBLEy57v2SYo","session_id":"d6d77a57-6575-434e-8636-d856c1e7216a","uuid":"69249067-79a4-49a6-9bfd-d544db60fe1c"}
