equirements responses\n- `cancelled_invocations()` - Query cancellation history\n\n**Implementations:**\n- `Default` - Creates fully available adapter\n- `AgentExecutionPort` trait:\n  - `check_capability()` - Validates stage/contract support\n  - `check_availability()` - Returns availability state\n  - `invoke()` - Executes invocation with configurable failures\n  - `cancel()` - Records cancellations\n\n**Canned Payloads:** Deterministic JSON responses by stage type:\n- **Planning stages** (PromptReview, Planning, DocsPlan, CiPlan):\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"problem_framing\": \"...\",\n    \"assumptions_or_open_questions\": [...],\n    \"proposed_work\": [...],\n    \"readiness\": { \"ready\": true, \"risks\": [] }\n  }\n  ```\n- **Implementation stages** (Implementation, PlanAndImplement, ApplyFixes, DocsUpdate, CiUpdate):\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"change_summary\": \"...\",\n    \"steps\": [...],\n    \"validation_evidence\": [...],\n    \"outstanding_risks\": []\n  }\n  ```\n- **Validation/Review stages** (Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview, DocsValidation, CiValidation):\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"outcome\": \"approved\",\n    \"evidence\": [...],\n    \"findings_or_gaps\": [],\n    \"follow_up_or_amendments\": []\n  }\n  ```\n- **Requirements contracts:**\n  - `question_set` → `{ \"questions\": [] }`\n  - `requirements_draft` → `{ \"problem_summary\": \"...\", \"goals\": [...], ... }`\n  - `requirements_review` → `{ \"outcome\": \"approved\", ... }`\n  - `project_seed` → `{ \"project_id\": \"...\", \"flow\": \"...\", ... }`\n\n---\n\n### 9. `src/cli/mod.rs` - CLI Structure\n\n**44 lines - Central CLI router**\n\n**Modules:** 8 subcommand handlers\n```rust\npub mod config;\npub mod conformance;\npub mod daemon;\npub mod flow;\npub mod init;\npub mod project;\npub mod requirements;\npub mod run;\n```\n\n**Cli struct (with Clap derive):**\n- `command: Commands` - Subcommand enum\n\n**Commands enum (8 variants):**\n1. `Init(init::InitCommand)` - Workspace initialization\n2. `Flow(flow::FlowCommand)` - Flow discovery\n3. `Config(config::ConfigCommand)` - Workspace config\n4. `Project(project::ProjectCommand)` - Project CRUD\n5. `Run(run::RunCommand)` - Run orchestration\n6. `Requirements(requirements::RequirementsCommand)` - Requirements drafting\n7. `Daemon(daemon::DaemonCommand)` - Daemon management\n8. `Conformance(conformance::ConformanceCommand)` - **STUB** ← Conformance testing\n\n**run() function:** Async dispatcher that matches command and calls appropriate handler\n\n**Naming convention:**\n- Command structs: `XyzCommand` (implements `Args`)\n- Subcommand enums: `XyzSubcommand` (implements `Subcommand`)\n- Handler functions: `async fn handle(command: XyzCommand) -> AppResult<()>`\n\n---\n\n### 10. `src/main.rs` - Application Entry Point\n\n**30 lines - Minimal bootstrap**\n\n```rust\n#![forbid(unsafe_code)]\n\nuse std::process::ExitCode;\nuse clap::Parser;\nuse ralph_burning::cli::{self, Cli};\n\n#[tokio::main(flavor = \"multi_thread\")]\nasync fn main() -> ExitCode {\n    init_tracing();\n\n    let cli = Cli::parse();\n\n    match cli::run(cli).await {\n        Ok(()) => ExitCode::SUCCESS,\n        Err(error) => {\n            eprintln!(\"{error}\");\n            ExitCode::FAILURE\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nfn init_tracing() {\n    let _ = tracing_subscriber::fmt()\n        .compact()\n        .with_target(false)\n        .without_time()\n        .try_init();\n}\n```\n\n**Key aspects:**\n- Multi-threaded async runtime (Tokio)\n- Forbids unsafe code at crate level\n- Minimal error handling - errors printed to stderr\n- Simple structured logging initialization (compact format, no targets/times)\n- Exit codes: 0 = success, 1 = failure\n\n---\n\n### 11. `tests/unit/` Directory Structure\n\n**Location:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/`\n\n**19 test files (447 KB total):**\n\n| File | Size | Focus |\n|------|------|-------|\n| `workflow_engine_test.rs` | 113,412 bytes | Stage orchestrat