{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013YHMY8sGEWr7uM3xrMG2kM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Feature: Daemon Routing and Leases\n     2→  The daemon routes tasks to built-in flows, enforces task and lease invariants,\n     3→  and reconciles stale daemon state under `.ralph-burning/daemon/`.\n     4→\n     5→  # DAEMON-ROUTING-001\n     6→  Scenario: Routing precedence prefers command over labels and workspace default\n     7→    Given a daemon task with routing command \"/rb flow quick_dev\"\n     8→    And the task has routing label \"rb:flow:docs_change\"\n     9→    And the workspace default flow is \"standard\"\n    10→    When the daemon resolves task routing\n    11→    Then the selected flow is \"quick_dev\"\n    12→    And the routing source is \"command\"\n    13→\n    14→  # DAEMON-ROUTING-002\n    15→  Scenario: Valid routing labels select the flow when no command is present\n    16→    Given a daemon task with routing labels:\n    17→      | rb:flow:docs_change |\n    18→    And the workspace default flow is \"standard\"\n    19→    When the daemon resolves task routing\n    20→    Then the selected flow is \"docs_change\"\n    21→    And the routing source is \"label\"\n    22→\n    23→  # DAEMON-ROUTING-003\n    24→  Scenario: Malformed routing labels are ignored with a warning\n    25→    Given a daemon task with routing labels:\n    26→      | rb:flow          |\n    27→      | rb:flow:standard |\n    28→    When the daemon resolves task routing\n    29→    Then the selected flow is \"standard\"\n    30→    And the daemon records a routing warning\n    31→\n    32→  # DAEMON-ROUTING-004\n    33→  Scenario: Conflicting routing labels fail task creation\n    34→    Given a daemon task with routing labels:\n    35→      | rb:flow:standard   |\n    36→      | rb:flow:quick_dev  |\n    37→    When the task is created through the daemon task service\n    38→    Then task creation fails with \"AmbiguousRouting\"\n    39→\n    40→  # DAEMON-ROUTING-005\n    41→  Scenario: Duplicate non-terminal issue task is rejected\n    42→    Given a daemon task already exists for issue \"repo#101\" in status \"pending\"\n    43→    When another task is created for issue \"repo#101\"\n    44→    Then task creation fails with \"DuplicateTaskForIssue\"\n    45→\n    46→  # DAEMON-ROUTING-006\n    47→  Scenario: Lease acquisition claims the task and creates a worktree lease\n    48→    Given a pending daemon task with a valid routed flow\n    49→    When the daemon claims the task\n    50→    Then the task transitions to \"claimed\"\n    51→    And a worktree lease is persisted under \".ralph-burning/daemon/leases/\"\n    52→    And the task references the persisted lease id\n    53→\n    54→  # DAEMON-ROUTING-007\n    55→  Scenario: Reconciliation fails claimed tasks with stale leases\n    56→    Given a claimed daemon task with a stale worktree lease heartbeat\n    57→    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon reconcile\"\n    58→    Then the stale lease is released\n    59→    And the orphaned worktree is removed\n    60→    And the task transitions to \"failed\"\n    61→    And the failure class is \"reconciliation_timeout\"\n    62→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d6d77a57-6575-434e-8636-d856c1e7216a","uuid":"1d3e2451-9281-4607-b292-c62812919856","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/daemon_routing.feature","content":"Feature: Daemon Routing and Leases\n  The daemon routes tasks to built-in flows, enforces task and lease invariants,\n  and reconciles stale daemon state under `.ralph-burning/daemon/`.\n\n  # DAEMON-ROUTING-001\n  Scenario: Routing precedence prefers command over labels and workspace default\n    Given a daemon task with routing command \"/rb flow quick_dev\"\n    And the task has routing label \"rb:flow:docs_change\"\n    And the workspace default flow is \"standard\"\n    When the daemon resolves task routing\n    Then the selected flow is \"quick_dev\"\n    And the routing source is \"command\"\n\n  # DAEMON-ROUTING-002\n  Scenario: Valid routing labels select the flow when no command is present\n    Given a daemon task with routing labels:\n      | rb:flow:docs_change |\n    And the workspace default flow is \"standard\"\n    When the daemon resolves task routing\n    Then the selected flow is \"docs_change\"\n    And the routing source is \"label\"\n\n  # DAEMON-ROUTING-003\n  Scenario: Malformed routing labels are ignored with a warning\n    Given a daemon task with routing labels:\n      | rb:flow          |\n      | rb:flow:standard |\n    When the daemon resolves task routing\n    Then the selected flow is \"standard\"\n    And the daemon records a routing warning\n\n  # DAEMON-ROUTING-004\n  Scenario: Conflicting routing labels fail task creation\n    Given a daemon task with routing labels:\n      | rb:flow:standard   |\n      | rb:flow:quick_dev  |\n    When the task is created through the daemon task service\n    Then task creation fails with \"AmbiguousRouting\"\n\n  # DAEMON-ROUTING-005\n  Scenario: Duplicate non-terminal issue task is rejected\n    Given a daemon task already exists for issue \"repo#101\" in status \"pending\"\n    When another task is created for issue \"repo#101\"\n    Then task creation fails with \"DuplicateTaskForIssue\"\n\n  # DAEMON-ROUTING-006\n  Scenario: Lease acquisition claims the task and creates a worktree lease\n    Given a pending daemon task with a valid routed flow\n    When the daemon claims the task\n    Then the task transitions to \"claimed\"\n    And a worktree lease is persisted under \".ralph-burning/daemon/leases/\"\n    And the task references the persisted lease id\n\n  # DAEMON-ROUTING-007\n  Scenario: Reconciliation fails claimed tasks with stale leases\n    Given a claimed daemon task with a stale worktree lease heartbeat\n    When the user runs \"ralph-burning daemon reconcile\"\n    Then the stale lease is released\n    And the orphaned worktree is removed\n    And the task transitions to \"failed\"\n    And the failure class is \"reconciliation_timeout\"\n","numLines":62,"startLine":1,"totalLines":62}}}
