{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011PjXazg6QnSEmXhKhe4nTQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→@active-project\n     2→Feature: Active project resolution\n     3→  The workspace tracks the currently selected project through the\n     4→  \".ralph-burning/active-project\" pointer file.\n     5→\n     6→  @active-project-select-existing\n     7→  Scenario: select an existing project\n     8→    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n     9→    And the project \"alpha\" exists under \".ralph-burning/projects/\"\n    10→    When I run \"ralph-burning project select alpha\"\n    11→    Then the output should include \"Selected project alpha\"\n    12→    And the file \".ralph-burning/active-project\" should include \"alpha\"\n    13→\n    14→  @active-project-select-missing\n    15→  Scenario: select a non-existing project\n    16→    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n    17→    When I run \"ralph-burning project select missing\"\n    18→    Then the command should fail with a clear project-not-found error\n    19→\n    20→  @active-project-missing\n    21→  Scenario: resolve when no active project is set\n    22→    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n    23→    And the file \".ralph-burning/active-project\" does not exist\n    24→    When a command requires the active project\n    25→    Then the command should fail with a clear no-active-project error naming \"project select\"\n    26→\n    27→  @active-project-resolve-valid\n    28→  Scenario: resolve after a valid select\n    29→    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n    30→    And the project \"alpha\" exists under \".ralph-burning/projects/\"\n    31→    And I run \"ralph-burning project select alpha\"\n    32→    When a command requires the active project\n    33→    Then the active project should resolve to \"alpha\"\n    34→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d6d77a57-6575-434e-8636-d856c1e7216a","uuid":"581e1731-1fcf-431b-b706-8ddeb459b9af","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/active_project.feature","content":"@active-project\nFeature: Active project resolution\n  The workspace tracks the currently selected project through the\n  \".ralph-burning/active-project\" pointer file.\n\n  @active-project-select-existing\n  Scenario: select an existing project\n    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n    And the project \"alpha\" exists under \".ralph-burning/projects/\"\n    When I run \"ralph-burning project select alpha\"\n    Then the output should include \"Selected project alpha\"\n    And the file \".ralph-burning/active-project\" should include \"alpha\"\n\n  @active-project-select-missing\n  Scenario: select a non-existing project\n    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n    When I run \"ralph-burning project select missing\"\n    Then the command should fail with a clear project-not-found error\n\n  @active-project-missing\n  Scenario: resolve when no active project is set\n    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n    And the file \".ralph-burning/active-project\" does not exist\n    When a command requires the active project\n    Then the command should fail with a clear no-active-project error naming \"project select\"\n\n  @active-project-resolve-valid\n  Scenario: resolve after a valid select\n    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n    And the project \"alpha\" exists under \".ralph-burning/projects/\"\n    And I run \"ralph-burning project select alpha\"\n    When a command requires the active project\n    Then the active project should resolve to \"alpha\"\n","numLines":34,"startLine":1,"totalLines":34}}}
