{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015XMtUYmEPBYrHge1YN9ckj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Feature: Completion Rounds, Late-Stage Acceptance, and Durable Amendments\n     2→  When a late stage (completion_panel, acceptance_qa, final_review) returns\n     3→  a non-approved outcome, the engine queues durable amendments and advances\n     4→  the completion round, restarting from planning. The completion guard\n     5→  blocks run_completed when pending amendments remain.\n     6→\n     7→  # SC-CR-001\n     8→  Scenario: Late-stage conditionally_approved triggers completion round advancement\n     9→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n    10→    And project \"cr-alpha\" is selected as active\n    11→    And the run snapshot shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n    12→    When the user starts a run where completion_panel returns \"conditionally_approved\" with amendments\n    13→    Then the engine queues durable amendment files under projects/cr-alpha/amendments/\n    14→    And the journal contains an \"amendment_queued\" event with the amendment body\n    15→    And the journal contains a \"completion_round_advanced\" event with from_round=1 to_round=2\n    16→    And the engine restarts from planning (stage_entered for planning appears a second time)\n    17→    And the planning invocation context includes pending_amendments\n    18→    And after successful planning commit the amendment files are removed from disk\n    19→    And the run snapshot shows completion_rounds=2 after completion\n    20→    And the run snapshot amendment_queue is empty\n    21→\n    22→  # SC-CR-002\n    23→  Scenario: Late-stage request_changes triggers completion round advancement\n    24→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-beta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    25→    And project \"cr-beta\" is selected as active\n    26→    When the user starts a run where acceptance_qa returns \"request_changes\" with amendments\n    27→    Then the engine follows the same completion-round path as conditionally_approved\n    28→    And the journal contains a \"completion_round_advanced\" event with source_stage=\"acceptance_qa\"\n    29→\n    30→  # SC-CR-003"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d6d77a57-6575-434e-8636-d856c1e7216a","uuid":"4598e432-b7b6-4068-a612-f4394b36e2b4","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_completion_rounds.feature","content":"Feature: Completion Rounds, Late-Stage Acceptance, and Durable Amendments\n  When a late stage (completion_panel, acceptance_qa, final_review) returns\n  a non-approved outcome, the engine queues durable amendments and advances\n  the completion round, restarting from planning. The completion guard\n  blocks run_completed when pending amendments remain.\n\n  # SC-CR-001\n  Scenario: Late-stage conditionally_approved triggers completion round advancement\n    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n    And project \"cr-alpha\" is selected as active\n    And the run snapshot shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n    When the user starts a run where completion_panel returns \"conditionally_approved\" with amendments\n    Then the engine queues durable amendment files under projects/cr-alpha/amendments/\n    And the journal contains an \"amendment_queued\" event with the amendment body\n    And the journal contains a \"completion_round_advanced\" event with from_round=1 to_round=2\n    And the engine restarts from planning (stage_entered for planning appears a second time)\n    And the planning invocation context includes pending_amendments\n    And after successful planning commit the amendment files are removed from disk\n    And the run snapshot shows completion_rounds=2 after completion\n    And the run snapshot amendment_queue is empty\n\n  # SC-CR-002\n  Scenario: Late-stage request_changes triggers completion round advancement\n    Given an initialized workspace with project \"cr-beta\" using flow \"standard\"\n    And project \"cr-beta\" is selected as active\n    When the user starts a run where acceptance_qa returns \"request_changes\" with amendments\n    Then the engine follows the same completion-round path as conditionally_approved\n    And the journal contains a \"completion_round_advanced\" event with source_stage=\"acceptance_qa\"\n\n  # SC-CR-003","numLines":30,"startLine":1,"totalLines":155}}}
