{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01DB8tf4wivdefkFEocyEYxw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0185VLPPQA13kzZJEW2yrmm6","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/project_records.feature"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1728,"cache_read_input_tokens":12214,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1728,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JZgEXfVjTEVJPd1ayi2jcT","session_id":"d6d77a57-6575-434e-8636-d856c1e7216a","uuid":"1200c581-33d4-4e8e-8504-2c4486bf79e0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0185VLPPQA13kzZJEW2yrmm6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Feature: Project Records\n     2→  Canonical project CRUD and immutable flow enforcement.\n     3→\n     4→  # SC-PROJ-001\n     5→  Scenario: Project creation writes all canonical files\n     6→    Given an initialized workspace\n     7→    And a readable prompt file \"prompt.md\"\n     8→    When the user runs \"project create --id alpha --name Alpha --prompt prompt.md --flow standard\"\n     9→    Then the command succeeds\n    10→    And the project directory \"alpha\" contains \"project.toml\", \"prompt.md\", \"run.json\", \"journal.ndjson\", \"sessions.json\"\n    11→    And the project directory \"alpha\" contains subdirectories \"history/payloads\", \"history/artifacts\", \"runtime/logs\", \"runtime/backend\", \"runtime/temp\", \"amendments\", \"rollback\"\n    12→    And \"journal.ndjson\" contains a \"project_created\" event with sequence 1\n    13→    And \"run.json\" shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n    14→\n    15→  # SC-PROJ-002\n    16→  Scenario: Duplicate project ID is rejected\n    17→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n    18→    When the user runs \"project create --id alpha --name Again --prompt prompt.md --flow standard\"\n    19→    Then the command fails with error containing \"already exists\"\n    20→    And the existing project \"alpha\" is unchanged\n    21→\n    22→  # SC-PROJ-003\n    23→  Scenario: Flow is immutable after project creation\n    24→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n    25→    Then \"project.toml\" for \"alpha\" contains flow \"standard\"\n    26→    And there is no CLI or store path to change the flow after creation\n    27→\n    28→  # SC-PROJ-004\n    29→  Scenario: Project list reads canonical records not directory names\n    30→    Given an initialized workspace with projects \"alpha\" and \"beta\"\n    31→    And \"alpha\" is the active project\n    32→    When the user runs \"project list\"\n    33→    Then the output includes \"alpha\" marked as active\n    34→    And the output includes \"beta\" not marked as active\n    35→    And each entry shows flow, status, and name from canonical records\n    36→\n    37→  # SC-PROJ-005\n    38→  Scenario: Project show displays explicit data\n    39→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n    40→    When the user runs \"project show alpha\"\n    41→    Then the output includes flow \"standard\", prompt hash, created timestamp, run summary, and rollback summary\n    42→\n    43→  # SC-PROJ-006\n    44→  Scenario: Project show resolves active project when no ID given\n    45→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n    46→    When the user runs \"project show\"\n    47→    Then the output includes project \"alpha\" marked as active\n    48→\n    49→  # SC-PROJ-007\n    50→  Scenario: Project delete succeeds when no active run\n    51→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" and no active run\n    52→    When the user runs \"project delete alpha\"\n    53→    Then the command succeeds\n    54→    And the project directory \"alpha\" no longer exists\n    55→    And \"project list\" does not include \"alpha\"\n    56→\n    57→  # SC-PROJ-008\n    58→  Scenario: Project delete clears active-project pointer if selected\n    59→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n    60→    When the user runs \"project delete alpha\"\n    61→    Then the command succeeds\n    62→    And the active-project pointer is cleared\n    63→\n    64→  # SC-PROJ-009\n    65→  Scenario: Project delete fails when project has active run\n    66→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" that has an active run\n    67→    When the user runs \"project delete alpha\"\n    68→    Then the command fails with error containing \"active run\"\n    69→    And the project \"alpha\" remains addressable\n    70→\n    71→  # SC-PROJ-010\n    72→  Scenario: Project creation is atomic\n    73→    Given an initialized workspace\n    74→    And a prompt file that will cause journal initialization to fail\n    75→    When the user runs \"project create --id partial --name Partial --prompt bad-prompt.md --flow standard\"\n    76→    Then the command fails\n    77→    And no partial project directory \"partial\" is visible to \"project list\"\n    78→    And the active-project pointer is unchanged\n    79→\n    80→  # SC-PROJ-011\n    81→  Scenario: Project create validates workspace version\n    82→    Given a workspace with unsupported version\n    83→    When the user runs \"project create --id x --name X --prompt prompt.md --flow standard\"\n    84→    Then the command fails with error containing \"unsupported workspace version\"\n    85→\n    86→  # SC-PROJ-012\n    87→  Scenario: Project create validates flow preset\n    88→    Given an initialized workspace\n    89→    When the user runs \"project create --id x --name X --prompt prompt.md --flow unknown\"\n    90→    Then the command fails with error containing \"unknown flow preset\"\n    91→\n    92→  # SC-PROJ-013\n    93→  Scenario: Project create does not implicitly select the project\n    94→    Given an initialized workspace\n    95→    When the user runs \"project create --id alpha --name Alpha --prompt prompt.md --flow standard\"\n    96→    Then the active-project pointer does not exist\n    97→\n    98→  # SC-PROJ-014\n    99→  Scenario: Project delete is transactional\n   100→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" and no active run\n   101→    When the filesystem delete partially fails after validation\n   102→    Then the project \"alpha\" remains addressable\n   103→    And the active-project pointer is unchanged\n   104→\n   105→  # SC-PROJ-015\n   106→  Scenario: Run.json contains full canonical run snapshot schema\n   107→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n   108→    Then \"run.json\" for \"alpha\" contains cycle_history, completion_rounds, rollback_point_meta, and amendment_queue fields\n   109→\n   110→  # SC-PROJ-016\n   111→  Scenario: Missing project.toml fails fast with corruption error on show\n   112→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n   113→    And \"project.toml\" for project \"alpha\" has been deleted\n   114→    When the user runs \"project show alpha\"\n   115→    Then the command fails with error referencing \"project.toml\" and \"missing\"\n   116→\n   117→  # SC-PROJ-017\n   118→  Scenario: Missing project.toml fails fast with corruption error on list\n   119→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n   120→    And \"project.toml\" for project \"alpha\" has been deleted\n   121→    When the user runs \"project list\"\n   122→    Then the command fails with error referencing \"project.toml\" and \"missing\"\n   123→\n   124→  # SC-PROJ-018\n   125→  Scenario: Missing project.toml fails fast with corruption error on delete\n   126→    Given an initialized workspace with a project directory \"alpha\" that has no project.toml\n   127→    When the user runs \"project delete alpha\"\n   128→    Then the command fails with error referencing \"project.toml\" and \"missing\"\n   129→\n   130→  # SC-PROJ-019\n   131→  Scenario: Project.toml records canonical copied prompt reference\n   132→    Given an initialized workspace\n   133→    And a readable prompt file \"external-prompt.md\"\n   134→    When the user runs \"project create --id alpha --name Alpha --prompt external-prompt.md --flow standard\"\n   135→    Then the command succeeds\n   136→    And \"project.toml\" for \"alpha\" contains prompt_reference \"prompt.md\"\n   137→    And \"project.toml\" for \"alpha\" does not reference the source path \"external-prompt.md\"\n   138→    And \"project show alpha\" displays \"Prompt reference: prompt.md\"\n   139→\n   140→  # SC-PROJ-020\n   141→  Scenario: Delete failure leaves project addressable\n   142→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" and no active run\n   143→    When the filesystem delete fails after the project has been moved to a trash path\n   144→    Then the project \"alpha\" remains addressable at its canonical path\n   145→    And the active-project pointer is unchanged\n   146→\n   147→  # SC-PROJ-021\n   148→  Scenario: Project select rejects schema-invalid project.toml\n   149→    Given an initialized workspace\n   150→    And a project directory \"partial\" with a syntactically valid project.toml missing required canonical fields\n   151→    When the user runs \"project select partial\"\n   152→    Then the command fails with error referencing \"project.toml\" and \"invalid canonical structure\"\n   153→    And the active-project pointer is unchanged\n   154→\n   155→  # SC-PROJ-022\n   156→  Scenario: Delete failure of active project leaves pointer unchanged\n   157→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n   158→    When the filesystem delete of project \"alpha\" fails\n   159→    Then the active-project pointer still points to \"alpha\"\n   160→    And the project \"alpha\" remains addressable\n   161→\n   162→  # SC-PROJ-023\n   163→  Scenario: Pointer clear failure during delete restores project\n   164→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n   165→    When the project \"alpha\" is staged for deletion but clearing the active-project pointer fails\n   166→    Then the command fails with an error\n   167→    And the project \"alpha\" remains addressable at its canonical path\n   168→    And the active-project pointer is unchanged\n   169→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JZgEXfVjTEVJPd1ayi2jcT","session_id":"d6d77a57-6575-434e-8636-d856c1e7216a","uuid":"84974312-1eee-4a20-8835-643afc66344f"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_progress","task_id":"a3dbe92d6d27e5cb7","tool_use_id":"toolu_01JZgEXfVjTEVJPd1ayi2jcT","description":"Reading tests/conformance/features/requirements_drafting.feature","usage":{"total_tokens":13966,"tool_uses":6,"duration_ms":2222},"last_tool_name":"Read","uuid":"ab0645cd-8dd9-465a-a5da-e60f448c966f","session_id":"d6d77a57-6575-434e-8636-d856c1e7216a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01DB8tf4wivdefkFEocyEYxw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017C1D165kygUPNpEqVCzkVS","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/requirements_drafting.feature"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1728,"cache_read_input_tokens":12214,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1728,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JZgEXfVjTEVJPd1ayi2jcT","session_id":"d6d77a57-6575-434e-8636-d856c1e7216a","uuid":"68e4cb90-6d2c-4f75-b508-176740e6248f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017C1D165kygUPNpEqVCzkVS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Feature: Requirements Drafting and Project Seed Handoff\n     2→  The `requirements` command family drives idea-to-seed workflows. Draft mode\n     3→  generates clarifying questions and waits for user answers before proceeding.\n     4→  Quick mode skips questions entirely. Both modes pass through a draft, review,\n     5→  and seed generation pipeline, persisting validated payloads, artifacts, and\n     6→  seed files at durable boundaries.\n     7→\n     8→  # RD-001\n     9→  Scenario: Draft mode generates clarifying questions\n    10→    Given a workspace with an initialized project\n    11→    When the user runs \"requirements draft --idea 'Build a REST API'\"\n    12→    Then a requirements run is created in draft mode\n    13→    And clarifying questions are generated\n    14→    And the run transitions to \"awaiting_answers\" status\n    15→    And an answers.toml template is written to the run directory\n    16→\n    17→  # RD-002\n    18→  Scenario: Draft mode with empty questions skips to completion\n    19→    Given a workspace with an initialized project\n    20→    When the user runs \"requirements draft --idea 'Simple change'\"\n    21→    And the backend returns an empty question set\n    22→    Then the run continues directly through draft, review, and seed\n    23→    And the run status is \"completed\"\n    24→\n    25→  # RD-003\n    26→  Scenario: Quick mode skips questions entirely\n    27→    Given a workspace with an initialized project\n    28→    When the user runs \"requirements quick --idea 'Build a REST API'\"\n    29→    Then no question set is generated\n    30→    And the pipeline proceeds directly to draft, review, and seed\n    31→    And the run status is \"completed\"\n    32→    And seed files are written to the run directory\n    33→\n    34→  # RD-004\n    35→  Scenario: Answer submission validates required answers\n    36→    Given a requirements run in \"awaiting_answers\" status\n    37→    When the user runs \"requirements answer <run-id>\"\n    38→    Then the TOML answers file is opened in $EDITOR\n    39→    And answers are validated against the question set\n    40→    And the pipeline resumes from draft, review, and seed\n    41→\n    42→  # RD-005\n    43→  Scenario: Show displays run state\n    44→    Given a completed requirements run\n    45→    When the user runs \"requirements show <run-id>\"\n    46→    Then the run status, mode, and seed path are displayed\n    47→\n    48→  # RD-006\n    49→  Scenario: Review rejection fails the run\n    50→    Given a requirements run in progress\n    51→    When the review stage returns \"request_changes\" outcome\n    52→    Then the run transitions to \"failed\" status\n    53→    And the review payload and artifact are still persisted\n    54→\n    55→  # RD-007\n    56→  Scenario: Seed rollback on prompt write failure\n    57→    Given a requirements run that reached seed generation\n    58→    When the seed prompt.md write fails after project.json succeeds\n    59→    Then both seed files are removed via rollback\n    60→    And the run transitions to \"failed\" status\n    61→\n    62→  # RD-008\n    63→  Scenario: Contract validation rejects duplicate question IDs\n    64→    Given a question set payload with duplicate question IDs\n    65→    When the payload is validated through the question_set contract\n    66→    Then a domain validation error is returned\n    67→\n    68→  # RD-009\n    69→  Scenario: Contract validation rejects non-approval outcome without findings\n    70→    Given a review payload with \"rejected\" outcome and empty findings\n    71→    When the payload is validated through the requirements_review contract\n    72→    Then a domain validation error is returned\n    73→\n    74→  # RD-010\n    75→  Scenario: Failed run can be resumed via answer\n    76→    Given a requirements run in \"failed\" status with a committed question set\n    77→    When the user runs \"requirements answer <run-id>\"\n    78→    Then the pipeline resumes from the answer boundary\n    79→\n    80→  # RD-011\n    81→  Scenario: Editor failure preserves run state\n    82→    Given a requirements run in \"awaiting_answers\" status\n    83→    When the user runs \"requirements answer <run-id>\"\n    84→    And $EDITOR exits with a non-zero status\n    85→    Then the run state remains \"awaiting_answers\"\n    86→    And the journal has no new events\n    87→    And answers.json is not replaced\n    88→\n    89→  # RD-012\n    90→  Scenario: Answer validation rejects unknown question IDs\n    91→    Given a requirements run in \"awaiting_answers\" status with a committed question set\n    92→    When the user provides an answers.toml containing keys not in the question set\n    93→    Then an answer validation error is returned\n    94→    And answers.json is not replaced\n    95→    And the run remains at the same committed question boundary\n    96→\n    97→  # RD-013\n    98→  Scenario: Answer validation rejects empty required answers\n    99→    Given a requirements run in \"awaiting_answers\" status with required questions\n   100→    When the user provides an answers.toml with empty values for required questions\n   101→    Then an answer validation error is returned\n   102→    And answers.json is not replaced\n   103→    And the run remains at the same committed question boundary\n   104→\n   105→  # RD-014\n   106→  Scenario: Conditional approval includes follow-ups in seed\n   107→    Given a requirements run whose review returns \"conditionally_approved\" with follow-ups\n   108→    When the pipeline reaches seed generation\n   109→    Then the persisted seed payload includes the review follow-ups\n   110→    And the rendered handoff summary includes the follow-ups\n   111→    And the run status is \"completed\"\n   112→\n   113→  # RD-015\n   114→  Scenario: Answer rejected when answers already durably submitted\n   115→    Given a requirements run in \"failed\" status with a committed question set\n   116→    And the journal contains an \"answers_submitted\" event\n   117→    When the user runs \"requirements answer <run-id>\"\n   118→    Then an invalid requirements state error is returned\n   119→    And the run state remains \"failed\"\n   120→    And no new journal events are appended\n   121→\n   122→  # RD-016\n   123→  Scenario: Empty-question draft still records question-set boundary\n   124→    Given a workspace with an initialized project\n   125→    When the user runs \"requirements draft --idea 'Simple change'\"\n   126→    And the backend returns an empty question set\n   127→    Then the run.json contains a non-null latest_question_set_id\n   128→    And the journal contains a \"questions_generated\" event\n   129→    And the run status is \"completed\"\n   130→\n   131→  # RD-017\n   132→  Scenario: Conditional approval with empty follow-ups fails contract validation\n   133→    Given a requirements review payload with \"conditionally_approved\" outcome\n   134→    And the payload has an empty follow_ups list\n   135→    When the payload is validated through the requirements_review contract\n   136→    Then a domain validation error is returned\n   137→    And the error mentions \"conditionally_approved requires at least one follow-up\"\n   138→\n   139→  # RD-018\n   140→  Scenario: Answer durable-boundary gating prevents double submission\n   141→    Given a requirements run in \"awaiting_answers\" status\n   142→    And the journal already contains an \"answers_submitted\" event\n   143→    When the user runs \"requirements answer <run-id>\"\n   144→    Then an invalid requirements state error is returned\n   145→    And the run state remains unchanged\n   146→\n   147→  # RD-019\n   148→  Scenario: Quick-mode run persists answers.toml and answers.json\n   149→    Given a workspace with an initialized project\n   150→    When the user runs \"requirements quick --idea 'Build a REST API'\"\n   151→    Then the run directory contains \"answers.toml\"\n   152→    And the run directory contains \"answers.json\"\n   153→    And the run status is \"completed\"\n   154→\n   155→  # RD-020\n   156→  Scenario: Empty-question draft persists answers.toml and answers.json\n   157→    Given a workspace with an initialized project\n   158→    When the user runs \"requirements draft --idea 'Simple change'\"\n   159→    And the backend returns an empty question set\n   160→    Then the run directory contains \"answers.toml\"\n   161→    And the run directory contains \"answers.json\"\n   162→    And the run status is \"completed\"\n   163→\n   164→  # RD-021\n   165→  Scenario: Failed run at question boundary reports pending question count via show\n   166→    Given a requirements run in \"failed\" status at the committed question boundary\n   167→    And the run has a pending_question_count recorded in run.json\n   168→    When the user runs \"requirements show <run-id>\"\n   169→    Then the output includes the pending question count\n   170→    And the output includes the failure summary\n   171→\n   172→  # RD-022\n   173→  Scenario: Answer rejected when answers.json already populated\n   174→    Given a requirements run in \"awaiting_answers\" status\n   175→    And answers.json has been durably written with non-empty answer content\n   176→    And no AnswersSubmitted event exists in the journal\n   177→    When the user runs \"requirements answer <run-id>\"\n   178→    Then an invalid requirements state error is returned\n   179→    And the run state remains \"awaiting_answers\"\n   180→\n   181→  # RD-023\n   182→  Scenario: Seed write failure leaves no seed history behind\n   183→    Given a requirements run that reached seed generation\n   184→    When the seed file writes fail after draft and review history are committed\n   185→    Then no seed payload or artifact exists in history/payloads or history/artifacts\n   186→    And the run transitions to \"failed\" status\n   187→    And only the draft and review history survive\n   188→\n   189→  # RD-024\n   190→  Scenario: Show does not report stale pending questions after answer boundary\n   191→    Given a requirements run in \"failed\" status at question_round 2\n   192→    And the journal contains an \"answers_submitted\" event\n   193→    And run.json still has a non-zero pending_question_count\n   194→    When the user runs \"requirements show <run-id>\"\n   195→    Then the output does not include pending questions\n   196→    And the failure summary is displayed\n   197→\n   198→  # RD-025\n   199→  Scenario: Seed rollback persists terminal state before cleanup\n   200→    Given a requirements run that reached seed generation\n   201→    When the seed file write fails\n   202→    Then the run transitions to \"failed\" status before seed files are removed\n   203→    And canonical state is terminal even if cleanup is incomplete\n   204→\n   205→  # RD-026\n   206→  Scenario: Contract validation rejects question IDs with non-bare-key characters\n   207→    Given a question set payload with an ID containing spaces or dots\n   208→    When the payload is validated through the question_set contract\n   209→    Then a domain validation error is returned\n   210→    And the error mentions \"TOML bare keys\"\n   211→\n   212→  # RD-027\n   213→  Scenario: Answers template round-trips with special characters in prompts and defaults\n   214→    Given a question set payload with prompts and defaults containing quotes and newlines\n   215→    When the answers.toml template is generated from the question set\n   216→    Then the template is valid TOML\n   217→    And parsing the template produces the original default values\n   218→\n   219→  # RD-028\n   220→  Scenario: Journal append failure at run_created transitions run to failed\n   221→    Given a workspace with an initialized project\n   222→    When the journal append fails during the run_created event\n   223→    Then the run transitions to \"failed\" status\n   224→    And run.json is the authoritative record of the failure\n   225→\n   226→  # RD-029\n   227→  Scenario: Journal append failure at questions_generated rolls back and fails run\n   228→    Given a workspace with an initialized project\n   229→    When the journal append fails during the questions_generated event\n   230→    Then the question payload and artifact are rolled back\n   231→    And the run transitions to \"failed\" status\n   232→    And latest_question_set_id is cleared in run.json\n   233→\n   234→  # RD-030\n   235→  Scenario: Journal append failure at draft_generated rolls back and fails run\n   236→    Given a requirements run that reached draft generation\n   237→    When the journal append fails during the draft_generated event\n   238→    Then the draft payload and artifact are rolled back\n   239→    And the run transitions to \"failed\" status\n   240→    And latest_draft_id is cleared in run.json\n   241→\n   242→  # RD-031\n   243→  Scenario: Journal append failure at review_completed rolls back and fails run\n   244→    Given a requirements run that reached review completion\n   245→    When the journal append fails during the review_completed event\n   246→    Then the review payload and artifact are rolled back\n   247→    And the run transitions to \"failed\" status\n   248→    And latest_review_id is cleared in run.json\n   249→    And draft history survives the review journal failure\n   250→\n   251→  # RD-032\n   252→  Scenario: Journal append failure at seed_generated rolls back seed and fails run\n   253→    Given a requirements run that reached seed generation\n   254→    When the journal append fails during the seed_generated event\n   255→    Then the seed payload and artifact are rolled back\n   256→    And seed files are removed from the run directory\n   257→    And the run transitions to \"failed\" status\n   258→    And draft and review history survive the seed journal failure\n   259→\n   260→  # RD-033\n   261→  Scenario: Journal append failure at run_completed preserves completed state\n   262→    Given a requirements run that reached the completion boundary\n   263→    When the journal append fails during the run_completed event\n   264→    Then the run remains in \"completed\" status\n   265→    And all seed files and history are preserved\n   266→    And the journal contains seed_generated but not run_completed\n   267→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JZgEXfVjTEVJPd1ayi2jcT","session_id":"d6d77a57-6575-434e-8636-d856c1e7216a","uuid":"6ea0ec7e-2be2-476f-87ed-89049e87f976"}
