{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VHdfjJ8NPuTcYM4i1TXVWw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Feature: Quick Dev Run Start Orchestration\n     2→  The `run start` command executes the `quick_dev` preset on the shared\n     3→  workflow engine, persisting canonical payloads, rendered artifacts, journal\n     4→  events, and run snapshots at each durable stage boundary.\n     5→\n     6→  # SC-QD-START-001\n     7→  Scenario: Happy path quick_dev run completes all stages\n     8→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"qd-alpha\" using flow \"quick_dev\"\n     9→    And project \"qd-alpha\" is selected as active\n    10→    And the run snapshot shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n    11→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    12→    Then the command exits successfully\n    13→    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\" with no active run\n    14→    And the journal records \"plan_and_implement\", \"review\", \"apply_fixes\", and \"final_review\" in sequence\n    15→    And payload and artifact records exist for all 4 quick_dev stages\n    16→    And completion_rounds is 1\n    17→\n    18→  # SC-QD-START-002\n    19→  Scenario: Review request_changes restarts from apply_fixes\n    20→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"qd-bravo\" using flow \"quick_dev\"\n    21→    And project \"qd-bravo\" is selected as active\n    22→    And the review stage first returns \"request_changes\" with follow-up amendment \"fix the identified issues\"\n    23→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    24→    Then the command exits successfully\n    25→    And the journal contains a \"cycle_advanced\" event from cycle 1 to cycle 2 resuming at \"apply_fixes\"\n    26→    And the apply_fixes invocation includes the review follow-up amendment in its remediation context\n    27→    And the non-passing review payload and artifact remain in durable history\n    28→\n    29→  # SC-QD-START-003\n    30→  Scenario: Review rejected fails the run\n    31→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"qd-charlie\" using flow \"quick_dev\"\n    32→    And project \"qd-charlie\" is selected as active\n    33→    And the review stage returns \"rejected\"\n    34→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    35→    Then the command fails with error containing \"review\"\n    36→    And the journal ends with a \"run_failed\" event referencing \"review\"\n    37→    And the run snapshot shows status \"failed\" with no active run\n    38→    And the rejected review payload and artifact remain in durable history\n    39→\n    40→  # SC-QD-START-004\n    41→  Scenario: Final review approved completes normally\n    42→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"qd-delta\" using flow \"quick_dev\"\n    43→    And project \"qd-delta\" is selected as active\n    44→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    45→    Then the command exits successfully\n    46→    And the run snapshot shows status \"completed\"\n    47→    And the journal ends with a \"run_completed\" event\n    48→\n    49→  # SC-QD-START-005\n    50→  Scenario: Final review conditionally_approved triggers completion round restart\n    51→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"qd-echo\" using flow \"quick_dev\"\n    52→    And project \"qd-echo\" is selected as active\n    53→    And the final_review stage first returns \"conditionally_approved\" with follow-up amendment \"polish the edge cases\"\n    54→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    55→    Then the command exits successfully\n    56→    And the journal contains a \"completion_round_advanced\" event\n    57→    And the final-review conditionally_approved payload and artifact are committed before restart\n    58→    And the run restarts at \"plan_and_implement\" for the next completion round\n    59→    And completion_rounds is 2\n    60→    And cycle and completion-round counters are monotonic and independent\n    61→\n    62→  # SC-QD-START-006\n    63→  Scenario: Final review request_changes triggers completion round restart\n    64→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"qd-foxtrot\" using flow \"quick_dev\"\n    65→    And project \"qd-foxtrot\" is selected as active\n    66→    And the final_review stage first returns \"request_changes\" with follow-up amendment \"rework the implementation\"\n    67→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    68→    Then the command exits successfully\n    69→    And the journal contains a \"completion_round_advanced\" event\n    70→    And the final-review request_changes payload and artifact are committed before restart\n    71→    And the run restarts at \"plan_and_implement\" for the next completion round\n    72→    And completion_rounds is 2\n    73→\n    74→  # SC-QD-START-007\n    75→  Scenario: Preflight failure leaves all canonical state unchanged\n    76→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"qd-golf\" using flow \"quick_dev\"\n    77→    And project \"qd-golf\" is selected as active\n    78→    And the backend is unavailable for preflight\n    79→    When the user runs \"run start\"\n    80→    Then the command fails with error containing \"preflight\"\n    81→    And the run snapshot is byte-identical to its pre-run state\n    82→    And the journal is byte-identical to its pre-run state\n    83→    And no payload or artifact files exist\n    84→    And no sessions were created or modified\n    85→\n    86→  # SC-QD-START-008\n    87→  Scenario: prompt_review.enabled has no effect on quick_dev stage plan\n    88→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"qd-hotel\" using flow \"quick_dev\"\n    89→    And prompt_review.enabled is true\n    90→    When the stage plan is derived\n    91→    Then the plan includes exactly 4 stages: plan_and_implement, review, apply_fixes, final_review\n    92→    And no prompt_review stage appears in the plan\n    93→\n    94→  # SC-QD-START-009\n    95→  Scenario: Failed quick_dev run resumes from durable stage boundary\n    96→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"qd-india\" using flow \"quick_dev\"\n    97→    And project \"qd-india\" is selected as active\n    98→    And a previous \"run start\" failed after \"plan_and_implement\" completed and \"review\" exhausted retries\n    99→    When the user runs \"run resume\"\n   100→    Then the command exits successfully\n   101→    And the resumed run keeps the original run_id\n   102→    And the plan_and_implement stage is not re-executed\n   103→    And the first resumed stage is \"review\" with attempt 1\n   104→\n   105→  # SC-QD-START-010\n   106→  Scenario: Daemon task routed to quick_dev completes through workflow engine\n   107→    Given a daemon task routed to flow \"quick_dev\"\n   108→    When the daemon dispatches the task\n   109→    Then the task completes through the same workflow engine path\n   110→    And no UnsupportedFlow error is surfaced\n   111→    And daemon task/lease invariants are preserved\n   112→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JZgEXfVjTEVJPd1ayi2jcT","session_id":"d6d77a57-6575-434e-8636-d856c1e7216a","uuid":"53be9fb8-1fa7-40ee-8937-f64e273132a8"}
