{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018qnKxR7YWFATcLKoqpgxj3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→@workspace-config\n     2→Feature: Workspace effective configuration\n     3→  The CLI resolves workspace settings through compiled defaults and\n     4→  workspace.toml overrides, and validates mutations before persisting them.\n     5→\n     6→  @workspace-config-show\n     7→  Scenario: show effective config\n     8→    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n     9→    When I run \"ralph-burning config show\"\n    10→    Then the output should include \"[settings]\"\n    11→    And the output should include \"prompt_review.enabled\"\n    12→    And the output should include \"source: default\"\n    13→\n    14→  @workspace-config-get-known\n    15→  Scenario: get a known key\n    16→    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n    17→    When I run \"ralph-burning config get default_flow\"\n    18→    Then the output should include \"standard\"\n    19→    And the command should exit successfully\n    20→\n    21→  @workspace-config-get-unknown\n    22→  Scenario: get an unknown key\n    23→    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n    24→    When I run \"ralph-burning config get unknown.key\"\n    25→    Then the command should fail with a clear unknown-config-key error\n    26→\n    27→  @workspace-config-set-valid\n    28→  Scenario: set a valid key\n    29→    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n    30→    When I run \"ralph-burning config set default_flow quick_dev\"\n    31→    Then the output should include \"Updated default_flow = quick_dev\"\n    32→    And the file \".ralph-burning/workspace.toml\" should include \"default_flow = \\\"quick_dev\\\"\"\n    33→\n    34→  @workspace-config-set-invalid-value\n    35→  Scenario: set an invalid value\n    36→    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n    37→    When I run \"ralph-burning config set default_flow unknown_flow\"\n    38→    Then the command should fail with a clear invalid-config-value error\n    39→\n    40→  @workspace-config-set-invalid-key\n    41→  Scenario: set an invalid key\n    42→    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n    43→    When I run \"ralph-burning config set unknown.key value\"\n    44→    Then the command should fail with a clear unknown-config-key error\n    45→\n    46→  @workspace-config-edit-valid\n    47→  Scenario: edit workspace config with a valid result\n    48→    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n    49→    And EDITOR writes a valid workspace.toml update\n    50→    When I run \"ralph-burning config edit\"\n    51→    Then the command should exit successfully\n    52→    And the file \".ralph-burning/workspace.toml\" should include \"default_backend = \\\"claude\\\"\"\n    53→\n    54→  @workspace-config-edit-invalid\n    55→  Scenario: edit workspace config with an invalid result\n    56→    Given the current directory contains an initialized \".ralph-burning\" workspace\n    57→    And EDITOR writes an invalid workspace.toml update\n    58→    When I run \"ralph-burning config edit\"\n    59→    Then the command should fail with a clear invalid workspace.toml error\n    60→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JZgEXfVjTEVJPd1ayi2jcT","session_id":"d6d77a57-6575-434e-8636-d856c1e7216a","uuid":"0ba58108-b96b-45d7-9e23-5b953f7c2d47"}
