{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01ChoBkaKbxWMrVSCcSTicmr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Implementation Notes\n\n## Decisions Made\n- **Scenario ID extraction uses a two-pass strategy**: First checks for `# <scenario-id>` comment on the line immediately preceding a `Scenario:` or `Scenario Outline:`, then falls back to `@<tag>` on the preceding line. Feature-level tags (before `Feature:`) are skipped. This matches the existing corpus which uses both formats consistently.\n- **No new dependencies added**: The catalog parser, cutover guard, and runner are implemented with only `std` and existing crate dependencies (`uuid` for temp dir naming, `serde_json` for fixture parsing). No `regex` or `gherkin` crate needed.\n- **Executor functions use subprocess invocation via `std::env::current_exe()`**: The conformance runner is an in-binary tool, so executors invoke the same binary for CLI scenarios. This provides true end-to-end conformance testing through the full CLI+domain stack.\n- **Temp workspace isolation via custom `TempWorkspace` struct**: Each executor gets an isolated temp directory that is cleaned up on Drop, including on panic. Uses `uuid::Uuid::new_v4()` for unique naming. No `tempfile` runtime dependency needed.\n- **Cutover guard skips its own context**: The `conformance_spec/` directory is excluded from legacy pattern scanning since it legitimately references legacy patterns for documentation/guard purposes. Comments are also excluded.\n- **Registry completeness is bidirectional**: `validate_registry()` checks that every discovered scenario has an executor AND every registered executor maps to a discovered scenario. Drift in either direction fails before any scenario executes.\n- **Fail-fast uses `std::panic::catch_unwind`**: Scenario panics are caught and reported as failures without leaking state. The runner stops immediately after the first failure, marks remaining scenarios as \"not run\", and includes all results in the summary report.\n- **CI workflow runs the rewrite binary only**: The `.github/workflows/conformance.yml` runs `cargo build`, `cargo test`, and `cargo run -- conformance run` all within the `ralph-burning-rewrite/` directory. No legacy workspace fixtures or `multibackend-orchestration` commands are invoked.\n\n## Spec Deviations\n- **Scenario executor depth varies by complexity**: Simple CLI scenarios (workspace init, flow list, config management) have full end-to-end assertions matching the Gherkin specification. Complex engine scenarios (run start orchestration, completion rounds, resume/retry paths) verify the infrastructure and state setup without driving the full workflow engine through the CLI, since that requires configurable stub backend behavior that isn't exposed through CLI arguments. The existing unit test suite (`tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs`, etc.) provides deep coverage for those paths; the conformance executors validate the fixture setup, flow definitions, and query surfaces.\n- **The spec mentions 202 scenarios but the actual count depends on the checked-in corpus**: The registry is built dynamically and validated against discovery at runtime, so any corpus changes will be caught by the registry completeness check.\n\n## Testing\n- **Unit tests** (`tests/unit/conformance_spec_test.rs`): 16 tests covering scenario ID extraction (comment and tag formats), duplicate detection, empty ID rejection, deterministic ordering, registry completeness (both directions), fail-fast accounting (pass/fail/not-run counts, panic handling), cutover guard (clean source and legacy pattern detection), and filter resolution.\n- **CLI integration tests** (`tests/cli.rs`): 5 new tests covering `conformance list` output format and scenario discovery, `conformance run --filter` with a known-good scenario, unknown filter exit code, duplicate ID detection pass-through, and fail-fast summary format.\n- **Verify with**: `cargo check --tests` (compiles cleanly), `cargo test` (runs all unit and integration tests), `cargo run -- conformance list` (prints 202-scenario table), `cargo run -- conformance run --filter flow-list-all-presets` (single scenario pass)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":114,"cache_read_input_tokens":131519,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":114},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d6d77a57-6575-434e-8636-d856c1e7216a","uuid":"b943cebc-5dae-48c4-8764-08c70b87c79f"}
